  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhen using an ethclient with an HTTP endpoint, sometimes it is useful for the client code to handle specific HTTP or JSON-RPC error codes. As a specific example, after a 429 Too Many Requests error, the client should extract the specified backoff time from the response body and wait for at least that length of time before retrying.\r\n\r\nCurrently, go-ethereum returns both the status text and response body formatted into a single string passed into the error constructor here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/rpc/http.go#L145 . While it is possible to extract the status code and response bodies using regex or similar string processing methods, it would be much more user-friendly (and efficient) if these attributes could be accessed through casting the error to some concrete error type exported by the go-ethereum library.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nI would be happy to offer a PR to implement these changes.\r\n\r\nThe proposed API would be a new exported error type from the rpc package:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntype HTTPRequestError struct {\r\n\tStatusCode int\r\n\tStatus     string\r\n\tBody       []byte\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc (err HTTPRequestError) Error() string {\r\n\tif len(err.Body) == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn err.Status\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%v: %v\", err.StatusCode, err.Body)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen the requesting code would need to be modified to fill in the respective fields on error.\r\n\r\nClient code could use this error type like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nweiBal, err := ec.BalanceAt(ctx, wallet.address, blockNumber)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n\tif err, ok := err.(rpc.HTTPRequestError); ok {\r\n\t\tif err.StatusCode == http.StatusTooManyRequests {\r\n\t\t\tbackoff := extractBackoff(err.Body)\r\n\t\t\tselect {\r\n\t\t\tcase <-time.After(backoff):\r\n\t\t\t\treturn errRetryable\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\r\n\t\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```",
